  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 honest low-confidence, accepted with documented residual uncertainty)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Evidence confidence is approximately 50% due to limited experimental replicates and wide scatter in the power-law hemolysis model exponents; this is honestly documented throughout. The assessment team accepts the limitation as residual uncertainty because: (a) the relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) provides a conservative safety margin that absorbs the quantified uncertainty bounds, (b) independent bench testing corroborates the CFD ranking of worst-case operating points, and (c) the sensitivity analysis identifies the two dominant uncertain inputs so targeted follow-on testing can close the gap before final design freeze.",
